channel.title: Swapped CPUs and now it's not working
channel.description:
What the hell.
Any idea why swapping a processor will make my computer not boot? I had a Q6600 in there, and I'm upgrading to a QX6850.
Put it in. Turned it on. Computer turns on. But just stays there. All fans spinning. Nothing happening. Monitor black screen.
Put the old one in, everything's fine.
They're both LGA775 sockets, which my mobo has.
